  Modifications in this fork:
  - Added "Part II — Positive Human Patterns" (P1–P14): what to ADD to make
    writing read as genuinely human, not just which AI tics to remove.
  - Added human-factors-analysis.md: the analysis behind Part II, with verbatim
    excerpts from a calibration corpus of pre-LLM writing (1945–2015), across
    biology, computer science, mathematics, economics, statistics, psychology,
    and philosophy of mind.
  - Added a calibrated-confidence step, a positive pass, and a read-it-aloud
    (spoken-language) test to the process.
  - Integrated the skill as one renderer within Promptus.

  Part II is this fork's own contribution, licensed under GPL-3.0 with the rest
  of Promptus.
